title.narrative: Output 1.1: Strengthened health systems capacity to deliver quality rights based and gender sensitive maternal new born child andadolescent health care

description.narrative: ;Despite the COVID-19 pandemic, there was increase in coverage in most maternal and newborn indicators in 2021. Through UNICEF’s inputs, 93% of Primary Health Care facilities are providing the 5 signal functions of Basic Emergency Obstetric and Newborn Care and 92% of district hospitals are providing Comprehensive Obstetric and Newborn Care. With UNICEF’s financial and technical support,83% against target of 82% villages have at least one capacitated Village Health Worker offering integrated community health package.The rising resignation rate amongst Health Care Workers and demotivated workforce presented an important bottleneck to improving quality. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2022
